          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Payday and Predatory Loans Moratorium Act of 2020 </b></p> <p>This bill prohibits for one year efforts by a lender to collect on certain debts owed by a borrower affected by the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) pandemic. Specifically, lenders are prohibited from collection efforts against such a borrower with respect to (1) a loan with a nominal interest rate of 36% or more, and (2) a loan which the lender did not determine was affordable while allowing the borrower to meet basic living expenses and major financial obligations.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-04-17T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
